points.name: CN Tower
points.script: Welcome to CN Tower! This is where your journey begins.

points.name: CN Tower Edge Walk
points.script: Hey folks! Ever wondered what it feels like to lean off the tallest freestanding structure in the Western Hemisphere? That's the CN Tower EdgeWalk for you - a thrilling experience on a ledge originally built for installing the tower's antenna. Who's ready to step outside their comfort zone and see Toronto from a whole new perspective?

points.name: Rees Wave Deck
points.script: Alright everyone, check out this unique structure! It's called the Rees Wave Deck, designed to mimic the rolling waves of Lake Ontario. Did you know this area used to be industrial land, completely transformed into a beautiful public space?

points.name: Empire Sandy
points.script: Alright folks, check out the majestic Empire Sandy! Built in England in 1943 as a WWII minesweeper, she's now the largest Canadian-built sailing ship. Isn't it incredible to think she once cleared paths for naval convoys, and now she offers stunning views of the Toronto skyline?
